sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1618032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Acylates starch with a GFP tag for visualisation of localisation
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Leda Coelewij

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1467204
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
A variation of the part BBa_E0040 that has been made compatible for Golden Gate by removal of internal BsaI and BpiI recognition sequences.
Fluoresces under UV light when the gene is expressed.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Cara Deal
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Domestication for GoldenGate by removal of internal BsaI and BpiI recognition sequences.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Rv3037c
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Rv3037c is a genetic sequence which encodes for a possible acylation candidate protein which acrylates glycogen strands in bacteria. The genetic sequence is encoded in the standard pSB1C3 backbone.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Farhan Mitha Mark Elms

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1618028
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is synthetic a 5'UTR, omega (Tobacco Mosaic Virus. The chloroplast transit peptide provides subcellular localisation to the chloroplast.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Leda Coelewij

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1467101
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
35S is a plant specific promoter obtained from Cauliflower Mosaic Virus. The part is intended for use as a constitutive promoter for gene expression experiments.
The part is compatible with GoldenGate MoClo Assembly Standard (free from BsaI and BpiI recognition sequences).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Cara Deal
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Domestication for GoldenGate (Removal of internal BsaI and BpiI recognition sequences).
